1301.definition: [διατηρέω] from {{G1223}} and {{G5083}}; to watch thoroughly, i.e. (positively and transitively) to observe strictly, or (negatively and reflexively) to avoid wholly

1302.definition: [διατί] from {{G1223}} and {{G5101}}; through what cause ?, i.e. why?

1303.definition: [διατίθεμαι] middle voice from {{G1223}} and {{G5087}}; to put apart, i.e. (figuratively) dispose (by assignment, compact, or bequest)

1304.definition: [διατρίβω] from {{G1223}} and the base of {{G5147}}; to wear through (time), i.e. remain

1305.definition: [διατροφή] from a compound of {{G1223}} and {{G5142}}; nourishment

1306.definition: [διαυγάζω] from {{G1223}} and {{G826}}; to glimmer through, i.e. break (as day)

1308.definition: [διαφέρω] from {{G1223}} and {{G5342}}; to bear through, i.e. (literally) transport; usually to bear apart, i.e. (objectively) to toss about (figuratively, report); subjectively, to "differ", or (by implication) surpass

1309.definition: [διαφεύγω] from {{G1223}} and {{G5343}}; to flee through, i.e. escape

1310.definition: [διαφημίζω] from {{G1223}} and a derivative of {{G5345}}; to report thoroughly, i.e. divulgate

1311.definition: [διαφθείρω] from {{G1225}} and {{G5351}}; to rot thoroughly, i.e. (by implication) to ruin (passively, decay utterly, figuratively, pervert)

1314.definition: [διαφυλάσσω] from {{G1223}} and {{G5442}}; to guard thoroughly, i.e. protect

1315.definition: [διαχειρίζομαι] from {{G1223}} and a derivative of {{G5495}}; to handle thoroughly, i.e. lay violent hands upon

1316.definition: [διαχωρίζομαι] from {{G1223}} and the middle voice of {{G5563}}; to remove (oneself) wholly, i.e. retire

1318.definition: [διδακτός] from {{G1321}}; (subjectively) instructed, or (objectively) communicated by teaching

1319.definition: [διδασκαλία] from {{G1320}}; instruction (the function or the information)

1320.definition: [διδάσκαλος] from {{G1321}}; an instructor (genitive case or specially)

1321.definition: [διδάσκω] a prolonged (causative) form of a primary verb δάω (to learn); to teach (in the same broad application)

1322.definition: [διδαχή] from {{G1321}}; instruction (the act or the matter)

1324.definition: [Δίδυμος] prolongation from {{G1364}}; double, i.e. twin; Didymus, a Christian

1325.definition: [δίδωμι] a prolonged form of a primary verb (which is used as an alternative in most of the tenses); to give (used in a very wide application, properly, or by implication, literally or figuratively; greatly modified by the connection)

1326.definition: [διεγείρω] from {{G1223}} and {{G1453}}; to wake fully; i.e. arouse (literally or figuratively)

1327.definition: [διέξοδος] from {{G1223}} and {{G1841}}; an outlet through, i.e. probably an open square (from which roads diverge)

1329.definition: [διερμηνεύω] from {{G1223}} and {{G2059}}; to explain thoroughly, by implication, to translate

1331.definition: [διερωτάω] from {{G1223}} and {{G2065}}; to question throughout, i.e. ascertain by interrogation

1332.definition: [διετής] from {{G1364}} and {{G2094}}; of two years (in age)

1333.definition: [διετία] from {{G1332}}; a space of two years (biennium)

1336.definition: [διηνεκής] neuter of a compound of {{G1223}} and a derivative of an alternate of {{G5342}}; carried through, i.e. (adverbially with {{G1519}} and {{G3588}} prefixed) perpetually

1337.definition: [διθάλασσος] from {{G1364}} and {{G2281}}; having two seas, i.e. a sound with a double outlet

1338.definition: [διϊκνέομαι] from {{G1223}} and the base of {{G2425}}; to reach through, i.e. penetrate

1339.definition: [διΐστημι] from {{G1223}} and {{G2476}}; to stand apart, i.e. (reflexively) to remove, intervene

1340.definition: [διϊσχυρίζομαι] from {{G1223}} and a derivative of {{G2478}}; to stout it through, i.e. asservate

1342.definition: [δίκαιος] from {{G1349}}; equitable (in character or act); by implication, innocent, holy (absolutely or relatively)

1343.definition: [δικαιοσύνη] from {{G1342}}; equity (of character or act); specially (Christian) justification

1344.definition: [δικαιόω] from {{G1342}}; to render (i.e. show or regard as) just or innocent

1345.definition: [δικαίωμα] from {{G1344}}; an equitable deed; by implication, a statute or decision

1348.definition: [δικαστής] from a derivative of {{G1349}}; a judger

1349.definition: [δίκη] probably from {{G1166}}; right (as self-evident), i.e. justice (the principle, a decision, or its execution)

1350.definition: [δίκτυον] probably from a primary verb δίκω (to cast); a seine (for fishing)

1351.definition: [δίλογος] from {{G1364}} and {{G3056}}; equivocal, i.e. telling a different story

1352.definition: [διό] from {{G1223}} and {{G3739}}; through which thing, i.e. consequently

1354.definition: [Διονύσιος] from Διόνυσος (Bacchus); reveller; Dionysius, an Athenian

1355.definition: [διόπερ] from {{G1352}} and {{G4007}}; on which very account

1356.definition: [διοπετής] from the alternate of {{G2203}} and the alternate of {{G4098}}; sky-fallen (i.e. an aerolite)

1357.definition: [διόρθωσις] from a compound of {{G1223}} and a derivative of {{G3717}}, meaning to straighten thoroughly; rectification, i.e. (specially) the Messianic restauration

1359.definition: [Διόσκουροι] from the alternate of {{G2203}} and a form of the base of {{G2877}}; sons of Jupiter, i.e. the twins Dioscuri

1360.definition: [διότι] from {{G1223}} and {{G3754}}; on the very account that, or inasmuch as

1361.definition: [Διοτρεφής] from the alternate of {{G2203}} and {{G5142}}; Jove-nourished; Diotrephes, an opponent of Christianity

1362.definition: [διπλοῦς] from {{G1364}} and (probably) the base of {{G4119}}; two-fold

1365.definition: [διστάζω] from {{G1364}}; properly, to duplicate, i.e. (mentally) to waver (in opinion)

1368.definition: [διϋλίζω] from {{G1223}} and ὑλίζω (to filter); to strain out

1369.definition: [διχάζω] from a derivative of {{G1364}}; to make apart, i.e. sunder (figuratively, alienate)

1370.definition: [διχοστασία] from a derivative of {{G1364}} and {{G4714}}; disunion, i.e. (figuratively) dissension

1371.definition: [διχοτομέω] from a compound of a derivative of {{G1364}} and a derivative of τέμνω (to cut); to bisect, i.e. (by extension) to flog severely

1372.definition: [διψάω] from a variation of {{G1373}}; to thirst for (literally or figuratively)

1374.definition: [δίψυχος] from {{G1364}} and {{G5590}}; two-spirited, i.e. vacillating (in opinion or purpose)

1377.definition: [διώκω] a prolonged (and causative) form of a primary verb δίω (to flee; compare the base of {{G1169}} and {{G1249}}); to pursue (literally or figuratively); by implication, to persecute

1378.definition: [δόγμα] from the base of {{G1380}}; a law (civil, ceremonial or ecclesiastical)

1379.definition: [δογματίζω] from {{G1378}}; to prescribe by statute, i.e. (reflexively) to submit to, ceremonially rule

1380.definition: [δοκέω] a prolonged form of a primary verb, δόκω (used only in an alternate in certain tenses; compare the base of {{G1166}}) of the same meaning; to think; by implication, to seem (truthfully or uncertainly)

1381.definition: [δοκιμάζω] from {{G1384}}; to test (literally or figuratively); by implication, to approve

1382.definition: [δοκιμή] from the same as {{G1384}}; test (abstractly or concretely); by implication, trustiness

1383.definition: [δοκίμιον] neuter of a presumed derivative of {{G1382}}; a testing; by implication, trustworthiness

1384.definition: [δόκιμος] from {{G1380}}; properly, acceptable (current after assayal), i.e. approved

1385.definition: [δοκός] from {{G1209}} (through the idea of holding up); a stick of timber

1388.definition: [δόλος] from an obsolete primary verb, δέλλω (probably meaning to decoy; compare {{G1185}}); a trick (bait), i.e. (figuratively) wile

1390.definition: [δόμα] from the base of {{G1325}}; a present

1391.definition: [δόξα] from the base of {{G1380}}; glory (as very apparent), in a wide application (literal or figurative, objective or subjective)

1392.definition: [δοξάζω] from {{G1391}}; to render (or esteem) glorious (in a wide application)

1394.definition: [δόσις] from the base of {{G1325}}; a giving; by implication, (concretely) a gift

1395.definition: [δότης] from the base of {{G1325}}; a giver

1396.definition: [δουλαγωγέω] from a presumed compound of {{G1401}} and {{G71}}; to be a slave-driver, i.e. to enslave (figuratively, subdue)

1398.definition: [δουλεύω] from {{G1401}}; to be a slave to (literal or figurative, involuntary or voluntary)

1399.definition: [δούλη] feminine of {{G1401}}; a female slave (involuntarily or voluntarily)
